Package: mortalityAdherence
Type: Package
Title: Biometric Table Adherence Testing for Pension Funds
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Your", "Name", email = "your@email.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
  )
Description: Tools for actuaries to test the adherence of biometric mortality
    tables to observed data from pension funds. Implements 11 statistical tests:
    Kolmogorov-Smirnov (KS), Chi-Square, Wald Type I and II and Likelihood
    Ratio Tests (LRT) Type I and II under both Poisson and Negative Binomial
    models, and a Bayesian Credibility Interval test. Includes a built-in
    database of 10 biometric tables used in the Brazilian actuarial market
    (AT-2000bm, AT-2000m, AT-49M, AT-55m, AT-83ms, GAM71m, GAM83m,
    BR-EMS2010, BR-EMS2015, BR-EMS2021), and functions for loading custom
    tables, reading pension fund data, and displaying formatted results.
